last_episode_to_air.name: The Wedding
last_episode_to_air.overview: Wicky is called to a wedding and meets Brummie kingpin Bob Mammot, the King of Storage.

name: The Cleaner
overview: After CSI have done their stuff, the cleaner mops up the grisly remains. For Wicky, a bloodbath and the pub is all in a day's work.

episodes.name: The Widow
episodes.overview: Professional crime-scene cleaner Wicky has to mop up after a particularly grisly murder, but keeps being interrupted by people unexpectedly dropping in on the crime scene.

episodes.name: The Writer
episodes.overview: Novelist Terence has two problems: his gran recently passed away, and he has writer’s block. Wicky thinks these issues might be related.

episodes.name: The Neighbour
episodes.overview: When he brings the wrong keys to a crime scene, Wicky meets the neighbour - and might have met his match.

episodes.name: The Aristocrat
episodes.overview: Wicky arrives at a stately home to clean up a burglary gone wrong. But things aren’t what they seem, and Wicky’s morals are tested.

episodes.name: The Influencer
episodes.overview: Wicky visits a social media influencer with millions of followers and an unhealthy obsession with the 1980s.

episodes.name: The One
episodes.overview: Crime scene cleaner Wicky heads to the country to clean up a nasty mess in a holiday home, and bumps into his first ‘proper’ girlfriend.

episodes.name: The Transaction
episodes.overview: Wicky faces the ultimate test of self-control: a job in a pub, after he’s promised his new girlfriend he’ll stay off the booze.

episodes.name: The Clown
episodes.overview: Wicky is hired by a theatre where a male strip show has got out of hand. A self-important clown, a whimsical theatre manager and a broken fire alarm turn his day into a nightmare.

episodes.name: The Night Shift
episodes.overview: Wicky is called to a shooting in a technology shop, where he finds himself sharing the night shift with Kai, a shelf-stacking conspiracy theorist.

episodes.name: The Shaman
episodes.overview: Wicky is on his way to clean up after a tragic death at a stately home, but there’s a shaman on the scene as well, and he has his own mystical agenda.

episodes.name: The Statue
episodes.overview: Wicky is called to a quiet town where a row has broken out over a statue. Tempers in the town are running high, and it looks like things might turn nasty.

episodes.name: The Dead End
episodes.overview: A gamekeeper has been murdered in rural Wales, and it falls to Wicky to clean up the mess. He knows that whatever happens on the job, it’s important not to lose your head.

episodes.name: The Reunion
episodes.overview: Wicky finds himself on a job for an old childhood school friend, Justin, who it turns out has done rather well for himself.

episodes.name: The Baby
episodes.overview: Wicky attempts to clean a hut for a furious pregnant lady.

episodes.name: The Committee
episodes.overview: Wicky repeatedly offends a building full of elderly people. The committee will hear of this...

episodes.name: The Lighthouse
episodes.overview: Wicky’s called to a remote lighthouse, where all is not what it seems. Will he survive seagulls, jellyfish, sea monsters and folk music?

episodes.name: The Housekeeper
episodes.overview: Wicky heads to a crumbling, stately home ruled by Mrs Barton, its despotic housekeeper.

episodes.name: The Wedding
episodes.overview: Wicky is called to a wedding and meets Brummie kingpin Bob Mammot, the King of Storage.
